<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
 <head>
  <style type="text/css">
	#img1{
	   opacity:0.1;
	}
	#img2{
	   opacity:0.3;
	}
	#img3{
	   opacity:0.5;
	}
	#img4{
	   opacity:0.8;
	}
	img{
	     opacity:0.5;
	}
	img:hover{
	     opacity:1.0;
	}
	
  </style>
  <title>CSS Opacity Property Example</title>
 </head>
 <body>
 <h1>Image Transparency</h1>

  <img src="F:\NatureImage1.jpg" width="200" height="200" border="0" alt="Nature Image" id="img1">  &nbsp;<img src="F:\NatureImage1.jpg" width="200" height="200" border="0" alt="Nature Image" id="img2"> &nbsp; <img src="F:\NatureImage1.jpg" width="200" height="200" border="0" alt="Nature Image" id="img3"> &nbsp; <img src="F:\NatureImage1.jpg" width="200" height="200" border="0" alt="Nature Image" id="img4"> 

  <p>The opacity property is often used together with the :hover selector to change the opacity on mouse-over:</p>

  <img src="F:\RainbowImage.jpg" width="200" height="200" border="0" alt="Rainbow" id="image">   &nbsp;&nbsp; <img src="F:\NatureImage3.jpg" width="200" height="200" border="0" alt="Nature Image" id="image">  &nbsp;&nbsp;  <img src="F:\NatureImage2.jpg" width="200" height="200" border="0" alt="Nature Image 1" id="image">

  <p>The opacity property is often used together with the :hover selector to change the opacity on mouse-over:</p>

  <img src="F:\RainbowImage.jpg" width="200" height="200" border="0" alt="Rainbow">   &nbsp;&nbsp; <img src="F:\NatureImage3.jpg" width="200" height="200" border="0" alt="Nature Image">  &nbsp;&nbsp;  <img src="F:\NatureImage2.jpg" width="200" height="200" border="0" alt="Nature Image 1">
 </body>
</html>
